    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="681"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Léger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Republic of Haiti</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Spring Lake, N. J.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have just heard the report
                    of the sad carriage accident which befell on yesterday the President of the
                    United States, and am happy to know that he sustained no serious injury.</p>
                <p>Permit me to have recourse to your kind intercession to assure Mr. Roosevelt that
                    I, together with the American people, congratulate myself on his escape from so
                    great a peril.</p>
                <p>With my sympathies for the victims’ families, be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. N. Leger.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
